reviews.text: Nice little restaurant with great food. Price is reasonable. We enjoyed the eatigo discount and end up around $250/head. Was totally full and satisfied
nice lunch set with good coffee

Unfortunately not very impressed, style over substance. The food was uninspiring and one main turned up 20 minutes late. The unusual choice of crockery detracted from the experience as it just made it harder to eat, odd shaped bowls are fine for high end haute cuisine, not a green salad... dozy.
With passion on food. Reasonable price.3crouse lunch set only HK dollars 98.

Great service, but the food can be improved. The good dishes were fajitas, lamb shank, and linguini alla vongole. I would order them again when I come back to the restaurant.

The French onion soup was a bit watered down and blend. The squid was a bit over cooked.
